<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-A692F06D-10A9-4160-8CBC-E345ED636C31" version="3" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-A692F06D-10A9-4160-8CBC-E345ED636C31" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">11 How to install the CreateUSB tool</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="M140829-B204"><p class="- topic/p ">The CreateUSB tool is used to create an USB Key for the software installation on the system. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Usually this software needs to be installed only once. It can be used to create USB Keys for any software version of the system. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Installation</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="M140829-B207" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "><ph class="- topic/ph ">Required tools</ph></title><ul id="UL_25327753B5924A18BC16054230EF66A9" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_DBAA4209863D40EB81835A0B081B06AC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The Iso files with the system software. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="DownloadAndPrepareUSBkeyinstallation" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-BBED23FE-4C3C-4B89-B9AA-CBF2EAFBB049.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 11 Download and prepare the software packages for a USB key installation...?>11 Download and prepare the software packages for a USB key installation</xref>. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> In case you want to create a USB installation key for: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado 1630 with a release 3.2 or higher 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado 1650 with a release 2.6 or higher 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Colorado M-series 4.3 or higher 
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> You need a 64 bits version of windows 7, 8 or 10 with the Microsoft .NET 6.0.224.6.1 Framework installed on the workstation. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="Check.Net" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C09C1F38-A74C-40FD-A1B9-0BBBD00A3370.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 11 How to check which .NET version is installed?>11 How to check which .NET version is installed</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_7926EBA61BF5497C965A84ABCB4E8134" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">You need a tool to open or mount the iso file. For example 7-zip. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">An alternative is to burn the image C16XX-a.b.c.d _1650-APPL-WIN10.iso to DVD. 
</p></li></ul><note id="GUID-CB050FAC-9034-46BF-B7C4-C17069267617" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">To install this software you need administrator rights. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-47E13376-15A5-48A4-A0D7-20B2681528B6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Procedure</title><p class="- topic/p ">In this example we use 7-zip to open the iso file. In windows 10 you could mount the iso file as a CD/DVD drive. 
</p><table pgwide="1" id="GUID-64A4BE8C-5F6D-4508-B6D0-E98C3701F885" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="90*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Open C16XX-a.b.c.d _1650-APPL-WIN10.iso with 7-Zip 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-68D978C3-27E1-4DB0-AD3B-8B74F92F5215" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-235BDCD6-3753-48C8-A2AA-2CE932CB90F0-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-235BDCD6-3753-48C8-A2AA-2CE932CB90F0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the CreateUSB directory. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Extract. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Choose a location where you want to place the files. Example: d:\temp\createusb_installer. 
</p><fig id="GUID-0E01DA6B-7E9A-4D29-B49A-C2AD7119A599" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F3225784-76C3-4E98-8139-B79EA58F6914-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F3225784-76C3-4E98-8139-B79EA58F6914-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click OK. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Close 7-Zip. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">6 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Browse to the location where you unzipped the files. Example: d:\temp\createusb_installer. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">7 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Double-click CreateUSBsetup.exe.</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The following window displays : 
</p><fig id="GUID-7FDBAFFB-5489-4370-877E-380AFFC0C83A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-6F300872-3F8B-4A60-B473-73EF61D7647D-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-6F300872-3F8B-4A60-B473-73EF61D7647D-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">9 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Select the desired installer language. 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">10 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click OK. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The License Agreement window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-C387AF66-2E2D-44C3-98E9-F32CAC6B9F2E" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0ED95061-14B2-4688-82C6-5A569C6AF8F5-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0ED95061-14B2-4688-82C6-5A569C6AF8F5-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">11 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click I agree. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Choose Components window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-096EDCCB-F44B-4B62-B521-ACED93EFF5D8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-C8C36176-8DEC-40F5-885B-F9659DE21C8E-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-C8C36176-8DEC-40F5-885B-F9659DE21C8E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">12 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Next. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Choose Start Menu Folder window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-64A9D2A5-157B-4CC2-B078-244D11EF9A31" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-288BC11A-4EFC-4F12-AA82-CE870D55E92F-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-288BC11A-4EFC-4F12-AA82-CE870D55E92F-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">13 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Next. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The Choose Installation Location window displays: 
</p><fig id="GUID-A6E446D6-2214-4722-B1FD-A816ED9192D1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B78B5DE4-1BA5-447A-B4F5-60136C3EAFEA-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B78B5DE4-1BA5-447A-B4F5-60136C3EAFEA-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">14 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Install. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">After a few seconds, the Installation complete window displays : 
</p><fig id="GUID-93C993BA-6FB9-44B4-A9F8-23C910F62B9D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A7981F80-1AE0-4D20-BE7D-5EDB39E5C018-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A7981F80-1AE0-4D20-BE7D-5EDB39E5C018-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">15 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Click Close. 
</p></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-724C7F1C-09E3-4D8F-B77B-2B159E768314.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Installation</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>